I"Ä<h3 id="instruction-and-issues">Instruction and issues</h3>

<p>Hi everyone!</p>

<p>So, this instruction for windows user but for unix it will be easy, as always :)</p>

<p>First of all:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Need to create a repository <a href="https://pages.github.com/">GitHubPages</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>I decided to use <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/">Jekyll</a>  (Actually, it was first tool which have been found me.)</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Please install ruby gems <a href="https://rubyinstaller.org/">official site</a></li>
      <li>So, next step we should put the <a href="https://gist.github.com/agragregra/53d8b9cc22c3f14d6ad6dc536c66fe14">certificate</a> in a folder
        <h5 id="example-on-my-pc-cruby27-x64cacertpem">Example on my PC C:\Ruby27-x64\cacert.pem</h5>
      </li>
      <li>Please check  ruby -v Ð¸ gem -v (Run CMD as administration)</li>
      <li>Set sertificate use the command
        <h5 id="set-ssl_cert_filecruby27-x64cacertpem">set SSL_CERT_FILE=C:\Ruby27-x64\cacert.pem</h5>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<hr />

<ul>
  <li>gem install jekyll</li>
  <li>jekyll -v</li>
  <li>gem install bundler</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<ul>
  <li>create a folder Site anywhere on the disk (run CMD from this plase)</li>
  <li>jekyll new YourBlogName</li>
  <li>jekyll build</li>
  <li>jekyll s</li>
  <li>Good job! Your blog is available to link localhost:4000</li>
  <li>If you want to stop server just send CTRL+C in console</li>
</ul>

